version: 1
display_name: PHTN-50-000130 - The Photon operating system TDNF package management tool must cryptographically verify the authenticity of all software packages during installation.
global_description: |-
  Installation of any nontrusted software, patches, service packs, device drivers, or operating system components can significantly affect the overall security of the operating system. This requirement ensures the software has not been tampered with and has been provided by a trusted vendor.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - PHTN-50-000130
  srg:
    - SRG-OS-000366-GPOS-00153
  cci:
    - CCI-003992
  nist:
    - CM-14
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_photon_5:
    type: custom
    desc: The Photon operating system TDNF package management tool must cryptographically verify the authenticity of all software packages during installation.
    control_id: PHTN-50-000130
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      At the command line, run the following command to verify software packages are cryptographically verified during installation:

      # grep '^gpgcheck' /etc/tdnf/tdnf.conf

      Example result:

      gpgcheck=1

      If "gpgcheck" is not set to "true", "1", or "yes", this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      Installation of any nontrusted software, patches, service packs, device drivers, or operating system components can significantly affect the overall security of the operating system. This requirement ensures the software has not been tampered with and has been provided by a trusted vendor.
    remediation: |-
      Navigate to and open:

      /etc/tdnf/tdnf.conf

      Add or update the following line:

      gpgcheck=1
